3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the problem of fooling machine learning models. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for image classification and adversarial perturbation generation.
